1. install python
//silently installs a default, system-wide Python installation (from an elevated command prompt):
python-3.6.0.exe /quiet InstallAllUsers=1 PrependPath=1 Include_test=0


2. install virtual environment scripts:
on windows:
	pip install virtualenvwrapper-win
on mac/linux:
	pip install virtualenvwrapper

3. create virtual env
cd <into project directory>
mkvirtualenv <envname>
	use 'workon <envname>'' to switch between envs

4. install django: 
make sure we are in virtual env:
	cmd line should start with (envname) C:blah blah
pip install django

5. start django project: 
django-admin startproject <projectname>
cd into <new projectname dir>
